      "content": "but that's the thing... there is no \"real me\" left to come back. you can't fix something that isn't there. it’s like looking at an empty house and trying to turn the lights back on. the spark is gone. the person who could actually feel things, who could care about anything, they're just dead and gone. i'm just the shell that's left behind, and honestly, it feels more like a burden to even exist as this empty thing.",
